cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.AI. 

The paper deals with the problem of mobile landmark search, which involves computer vision and information retrieval techniques. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are the most likely categories. The paper also proposes a novel hashing scheme and uses sparse coding and optimization techniques, which are related to machine learning and artificial intelligence. Hence, cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also possible categories. Finally, the paper focuses on practical applications and presents experiments on real-world datasets, which suggests that it may also fit into cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
